                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/16264: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-26T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 26, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>425. Chungking’s 544, October 25, 6 p.m. It is suggested that, in your
                    discretion, as in the cases of recent instances of the endangering by Japanese
                    bombing of American properties, both official and private, you may care to bring
                    to the attention of the Foreign Minister the bombing described in Chungking’s
                    telegram under reference which jeopardized the American Embassy and the U. S. S.
                        <hi rend="italic">Tutuila</hi> at that place and damaged American property
                        there.<note n="45" xml:id="d1010fn45">This was done in a note handed on
                        October 28 by the Ambassador in Japan to the Japanese Minister for Foreign
                        Affairs; see <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_699">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, Vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 699</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to Tokyo via Shanghai. Repeated to Chungking and Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
